HEADWORD: Chinoiserie
<hw>Chi`noi`se*rie"</hw> <pr>(sh⟦emac⟧`nw⟦adot⟧`z'*r⟦emac⟧")</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Chinese conduct, art,
decoration, or the like; also, a specimen of Chinese manners, art,
decoration, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a style in art reflecting Chinese influence, being
